        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "James Nunez",
          "email": "james.a.nunez@intel.com",
          "date": "2017-01-18 17:13:28.000000000",
          "tz": -420
        },
        "subject": "LU-1573 test: replay-ost-single test_9 issue extra write",
        "message": "LU-1573 test: replay-ost-single test_9 issue extra write\n\nThe proposed changes in the LU-1573 patch,\nhttps://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/16680, changes Lustre in a\nway that makes replay-ost-single test 9 hang. A sync write\nfrom the existing call to dd is executed after the fail_loc,\nthe file system is short on grants and the response is\ndropped. To modify replay-ost-single to pass with the new\nchanges to Lustre, we need to execute a write (dd) before\nthe replay_barrier so that the necessary grants are\nprocured before the fail loc and the file system should have\nenough grants to allow the sync write to proceed.\n\nSigned-off-by: James Nunez <james.a.nunez@intel.com>\nChange-Id: I3c0098e82a22660141d66e90fb175e5de60110ef\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
